comment._content: There is no corresponding entry on the CWGC website so it would appear that Private Alexander survived the war. There are 2 candidates in the MIC records: Pte 23974 East Surrey Regt or Pte 10889 in the E Surrey Rgt, later G/81279 The Queen's Regiment.

comment.author: 64288588@N05
comment._content: There is a George Herbert Alexander in the 1911 census who was born circa 1881 in Battersea, Surrey [sic]. At that time he was a Surveyor's Clerk living at 71 Kelmscott Road in Battersea, who had married Alice Gertrude in 1909 and had a newly born son Clifford George.
